The New Jersey Housing and Mortgage Finance Agency (NJHMFA) offers foreclosure prevention counseling for homeowners at no cost. This service is available statewide and provides assistance to homeowners who may be in default or at risk of defaulting on their mortgage payments, thus helping them avoid foreclosure. There are multiple field office locations throughout the state, including Atlantic, Bergen, Burlington, Camden, Cape May, Cumberland, Essex, Gloucester, Hudson, Hunterdon, Mercer, Middlesex, Monmouth, Morris, Ocean, Passaic, Salem, Somerset, Sussex, Union, and Warren counties. 

While operating hours are not explicitly stated, individuals can walk into any One-Stop Career Center or request an appointment for services. To qualify for services, individuals must have a physical, mental, cognitive, or other form of disability that constitutes a significant impediment to employment. This often requires documentation of their disability. Additionally, students with disabilities aged 14 and above can access Pre-Employment Transition Services without a formal application, though they need to be known to the DVRS.

Potential volunteers should reach out to the IRS for the nearest VITA site and additional information. There are prerequisites to volunteering, as participants may need to undergo training, but no specific identification or forms are mentioned in the information provided.
